"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code uses ax.set_xticks() and ax.set_xticklabels() with the unique dates from the DataFrame. However, this can lead to issues if there are too many unique dates, as it may not be appropriate to set all unique dates as ticks. Instead, it is better to use a locator that automatically handles the ticks based on the data range.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19,20\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%Y-%m'))\\n\"\n}"